  "prompt": "What percentage of questions are yet to be answered in Quora?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Quora does not publicly disclose the exact percentage of unanswered questions on its platform. The percentage of unanswered questions can vary widely depending on the topic, the specificity of the question, and how recently it was asked.\n\nQuora has millions of users, and questions range from highly popular ones that receive numerous answers to very niche or complex questions that may remain unanswered for longer periods. Additionally, some questions may be left unanswered because they are poorly phrased, unclear, or too obscure.\n\nIf you're looking for a specific answer or want to increase the chances of a question being answered, consider:\n\n1. **Clarifying Your Question**: Make sure it\u2019s clear and specific.\n2. **Targeting the Right Audience**: Ask in relevant spaces or invite experts in the field.\n3. **Engaging with the Community**: Answering other questions can increase your visibility and encourage others to answer yours.\n\nFor real-time statistics, you\u2019d need to look at Quora\u2019s internal analytics or inquire directly with their support team, though they may not share this data publicly.",
